# Sprint Documentation Locations

This document provides the locations of all sprint-related documentation in the Austin Shows Events project.

## Current Sprint

**Sprint 2: Ticketmaster API Integration**

The current sprint documentation can be found at:

- Primary sprint status document: `docs/sprint-status.md`
- Sprint 2 user stories:
  - US-D-001: Ticketmaster Import - `docs/user-stories/data/US-D-001-ticketmaster-import.md`
  - US-TH-001: Minimal Theme - `docs/user-stories/theme/US-TH-001-minimal-theme.md`

## Sprint History

- Sprint 1 summary: `docs/sprint1-summary.md`

## Sprint Planning

New sprint planning documents are created in the `docs/planning/` directory:
- Sprint planning template: `docs/planning/sprint-planning-template.md`
- Sprint 2 planning: `docs/planning/sprint2-planning.md`

## User Stories

User stories are organized by functional area:
- Data-related stories: `docs/user-stories/data/`
- Theme-related stories: `docs/user-stories/theme/`
- WordPress integration stories: `docs/user-stories/wordpress/`
- Technical infrastructure stories: `docs/user-stories/technical/`
- Search functionality stories: `docs/user-stories/search/`

## Acceptance Criteria

Each user story includes specific acceptance criteria that must be met for the story to be considered complete. These criteria are documented in the individual user story files.

## Test Documentation

Test documentation is available at:
- Test plans: `tests/docs/test-plans/`
- Test cases: `tests/docs/test-cases/`
- Test results: `tests/docs/test-results/`

## Updating Documentation

When working on the Austin Shows Events project, always refer to the most up-to-date documentation in the locations specified above. The `docs/sprint-status.md` file is the single source of truth for the current sprint status. 